'''Gert Joubert''' (born 1948 in [[Mowbray, Cape Town]]) is a [[Namibia]]n businessperson. Joubert was born in South Africa but moved to Namibia during the 1960s. While in university, Joubert was followed as a suspected [[communism|communist]] by the secret police of the apartheid regime until he approached the police and explained his support for [[capitalism]]. Joubert began his business career as a cattle entrepreneur near [[Otjiwarongo]]. In  2000, he ventured into [[eco-tourism]] and owns the [[Erindi Game Reserve]] near [[Omaruru, Namibia|Omaruru]] in the [[Erongo Region]].<ref>[http://www.economist.com.na/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=15538:the-capitalist-whom-they-mistook-for-a-communist&catid=554:archives The capitalist whom they mistook for a communist] [[Namibia Economist]], 27 October 2006</ref>

