[[File:Semi Koroilavesau.jpg|right|thumb|Koroilavesau in 2016]] '''Semi Tuleca Koroilavesau''' (born 1958)<ref name=ft2>{{cite web |url=http://www.fijitimes.com/story.aspx?ref=archive&id=90222 |title=SEMI Koroilavesau: Becoming a Director |publisher=Fiji Times |date=2008-05-25 |accessdate=2014-09-29}}</ref> is a [[Fiji]]an politician and Member of the [[Parliament of Fiji]]. He is a member of the [[FijiFirst]] party.
Koroilavesau grew up in [[Nalotu]] in [[Kadavu Province]].<ref name=ft1>{{cite web |url= |title=Semi Koroilavesau: the boy who grew up to be a businessman |publisher=Fiji Times |date=2008-05-25 |accessdate=2014-09-29}}</ref> He was educated at Yawe District primary school, Richmond High School, and [[Lelean Memorial School]].<ref name=ft1/> After sixth form, he joined the [[Republic of Fiji Military Forces|Fijian Navy]] as an officer cadet.<ref name=ft1/> In his military career he reached the rank of Commander. In 1988 he started a tourism company, [[Captain Cook Cruises, Australia|Captain Cook Cruises]],<ref name=ft2/> and in 2003 retired from the Navy to manage it.<ref name=ft1/>
Koroilavesau was elected in the [[Fijian general election, 2014|2014 election]], in which he won 1,611 votes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.electionsfiji.gov.fj/2014-election-results/ |title=2014 Election Results |publisher=Fiji Elections Office |date= |accessdate=2014-09-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140921200245/http://www.electionsfiji.gov.fj/2014-election-results/ |archivedate=2014-09-21 |df= }}</ref>
